==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbelief
<hw>Un`be*lief"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>belief</ets>: cf. AS.
<ets>ungele⟦aacute⟧fa</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The withholding of
belief; doubt; incredulity; skepticism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disbelief; especially, disbelief of divine
revelation, or in a divine providence or scheme of redemption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Blind <qex>unbelief</qex> is sure to err,⟦br⟧
And scan his work in vain.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Disbelief</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbelieved</ent>⟦br⟧
